data.name: Easy One-Pan Roasted Turkey with Vegetables
data.quickTastyDescription: A simple and wholesome dish featuring tender turkey and roasted vegetables, all cooked in one pan for effortless cleanup!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large bowl, combine the turkey breast, carrots, potatoes, and green beans.
Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and thyme over the mixture. Toss until everything is well coated.
Transfer the mixture to a large baking sheet or roasting pan, spreading it out evenly.
Roast in the preheated oven for about 60 minutes, or until the turkey is cooked through and vegetables are tender.
Remove from the oven, let it rest for 5 minutes, then slice the turkey and serve with the roasted vegetables.
